\f0\fs24 \cf0 Today is the birthday of  
\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Henry Cavendish
\f0\b0  \cf4 (\cf2 1731-1810), English natural philosopher, scientist, and an important experimental and theoretical {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 chemist}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physicist}}. He is noted for his discovery of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrogen"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 hydrogen}}, which he termed "inflammable air". He described the density of inflammable air, which formed water on combustion, in a 1766 paper, 
\f2\i On Factitious Airs
\f0\i0 . {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antoine_Lavoisier"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Antoine Lavoisier}} later reproduced Cavendish's experiment and gave the element its name.\
\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 A notoriously shy man, Cavendish was nonetheless distinguished for great accuracy and precision in his researches into the composition of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atmosphere_of_Earth"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 atmospheric air}}, the properties of different gases, the synthesis of water, the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coulomb%27s_law"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 law governing electrical attraction and repulsion}}, a mechanical theory of heat, and calculations of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Density"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 density}} (and hence the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mass}}) of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earth"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Earth}}. His experiment to measure the density of the Earth has come to be known as the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cavendish_experiment"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Cavendish experiment}}.\
\
Cavendish died in 1810
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \cb3 \super  
\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \nosupersub (as one of the wealthiest men in Britain) and was buried, along with many of his ancestors, in the church that is now {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Derby_Cathedral"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 Derby Cathedral}}. The road he used to live on in Derby has been named after him. The University of Cambridge's {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cavendish_Laboratory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 Cavendish Laboratory}} was endowed by one of Cavendish's later relatives, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Cavendish,_7th_Duke_of_Devonshire"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 William Cavendish, 7th Duke of Devonshire}} (Chancellor of the University from 1861 to 1891).\
\
\'c9 oggi il compleanno di Henry Cavendish, celebre fisico e chimico inglese. Molte delle sue scoperte nel campo dell'{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elettricit%C3%A0"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 elettricit\'e0}} e del {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calore"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 calore}} non vengono pubblicate, tuttavia i suoi contemporanei ritengono straordinari i lavori editi e considerano lo stesso Cavendish un chimico e un fisico di primissimo ordine. Membro effettivo della {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Society"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 Royal Society}} e consigliere del {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Museum"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 British Museum}}, gode di un'ottima posizione sociale. Nel {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/1775"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 1775}} progetta l'{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esperimento_Schiehallion"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 esperimento Schiehallion}} per tentare una misurazione della {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Densit%C3%A0"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 densit\'e0}} della Terra. In chimica si interessa allo studio dei {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gas"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 gas}}, isola l'{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idrogeno"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 idrogeno}}, e fa un'analisi precisa dell'aria e la sintesi dell'{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acqua"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 acqua}} ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/1784"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 1784}}). In fisica misura la {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costante_di_gravitazione_universale"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 costante di gravitazione universale}}, deducendo la densit\'e0 media della {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terra"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 Terra}} ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/1798"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 1798}}) e, con {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Augustin_de_Coulomb"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 Coulomb}}, pu\'f2 essere considerato il fondatore dell'{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elettrostatica"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 elettrostatica}}.\cf2 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 Cavendish era noto per la sua natura riservata e il suo carattere estremamente timido. Conduceva da solo le sue ricerche e si racconta che quando un giorno una cameriera entr\'f2 per errore nella sua stanza, egli rimase cos\'ec sconvolto da quella inaspettata presenza da licenziarla in tronco. In seguito fece costruire dei soppalchi per andare da una stanza all'altra della casa senza essere visto. \
